page.title: 16Wildlife in Moy
page.content: Mainly Roe Deer with occasional Red Deer. Large populaion of smaller mammals such as voles and shrews. Some Red Squirrels beginning to make an appearance. Rabbits and a few Wild Goats. Bird life includes many woodland birds such as types of Tits, Robins, Finches(some Bullfinch), Pigeons and Woodcock. On the moorland there are many Grouse and a few Black Game. A couple of Capercailzie have been spotted. There are ducks on the Loch, (no Swans now). The larger island supports a Heronry, whilst Gulls inhabit the other. The area is rich in wild flowers, including foxgloves, wood anenome, allium, primrose, wild hyacinth, heathers and ericas. There are some areas with gorse, broom, rhodedendrons and azaleas.
